cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI. 

This paper discusses a software framework for query processing and optimization over heterogeneous data sources, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DB (databases) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on query processing and optimization, which are core concepts in database systems. cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) is also relevant as the paper discusses the modular and extensible query optimizer with built-in optimization rules. cs.SE (software engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses the architecture of the software framework. cs.PL (programming languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the support for a variety of query languages. Finally, cs.AI (artificial intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the support for optimization rules, which can be seen as a form of automated decision-making.
